1 B. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall consist
2 of the same persons who constitute the Board on Legislative
3 Compensation as provided by Section 21 of Article V of the Oklahoma
4 Constitution.
5 C. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall be
6 authorized to meet only on the same date as the Board on Legislative
7 Compensation.
8 D. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall set the
9 salary for each of the following elected officials:
10 1. The Governor;
11 2. The Lieutenant Governor;
12 3. The Attorney General;
13 4. The State Treasurer;
14 5. The State Auditor and Inspector;
15 6. The Superintendent of Public Instruction;
16 7. The State Insurance Commissioner;
17 8. The Commissioner of Labor; and
18 9. The members of the Oklahoma Corporation Commission.
19 E. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall not set
20 the salary for any of the officials identified in subsection D of
21 this section at an amount less than the salary in effect for such
22 officials as of January 1, 2025.
23 F. At its authorized meeting, the Statewide Official
24 Compensation Commission shall set the salary for each of the
